reviews.text:
Had a nice lunch date with my wife and daughter here. Salty‚Äôs is a great add to this strip mall area of Harmons. The burgers are good, tater tots are crispy, and my wife and daughter loved the onion rings. Chatted with the owner who is a good dude. I appreciate that they offer a gluten free bun. I do wish they offered GF fries. And yes, gratefully they have Coke products on tap.  But the burgers (quality ingredients I‚Äôm sure) are expensive. It‚Äôs hard to compete in an In-N-Out world where they have great supplier prices. But this is a different burger with well seasoned, quality hamburger. The patties were perfectly cooked‚Ä¶not dry like a lot of smash-style patties.

A couple things I would probably change. I personally like whole leaf lettuce on my burger instead of chopped up lettuce that simply won‚Äôt stay on the burger.  I also think the cheeseburger needs to have noticeable amounts of cheese. These burgers need more cheese! But the sauce is excellent and the grilled onions too. Worth going here. 5 stars to keep it up and good luck in the new space!
Very good smash burgers from a small family owned operation. Definitely will go back!

This unassuming burger was the best smash burger I‚Äôve had in a long time. I went with the garlic rosemary and definitely recommend. The garlic was subtle and the sauce paired so well with the juicy patties. I‚Äôll be back soon and please, Salty‚Äôs, keep making them exactly like this.

This was one of the best burgers I‚Äôve ever had. Ground beef from a local butcher and sauces made from scratch make this place to die for!  I got the garlic rosemary burger and it was amazing!! 10/10 burger spot!!

Got myself the OG classic style Saltys burger with onion rings. The burger was juicy and loaded with their tangy OG sauce, very savory and delicious. And the onion rings were perfectly golden, I can‚Äôt wait to come back.
